The paper proposes a new algorithm for contextual bandits, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper also discusses exploration-exploitation trade-off, which is a common topic in reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves optimization and information theory, which could fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
